---
title: Chicken Stir-Fry Tacos with Tangy Cabbage Slaw & Sriracha Mayo
description: We’re always up for a sweet and savory dinner pairing, and these tacos are just that. Chicken breast strips are cooked in a sweet soy glaze until the glaze is sticky and the chicken is tender. They’re stuffed into steamy tortillas, along with a tangy, cilantro-flecked cabbage slaw. Of course, we’d never skip out on taco toppings, and these ones don’t disappoint: There’s creamy, spicy sriracha mayo and crispy fried onions. It’s all ready in just 15 minutes—life is sweet (and savory), friends.
